ἓὸ. Amphiaraus: joint king of Argos with Adrastus, whose daughter Eriphyle he married. Foreseeing his death if he took part in the campaign against Thebes, he concealed himself, but his wife revealed his hiding-place to Polynices in return for 3 necklace. Amphiaraus perished in the attack and was afterwards worshipped as a prophet-god at Oropus. Cf. Cic. N.D. 2. 7 3 Soph. Electra, 840.
